#~ "<h2>Highlights</h2> <p> This is a <em>wall</em> deck using Gangrel"
#~ " %(gangrel)s barons. It builds a strong defense thanks to "
#~ "the Anarch and Baron cards for unlock and intercept, "
#~ "%(organized_resistance)s and %(deep_ecology)s, coupled with %(bait_and_switch)s "
#~ "for bounces. </p> <p> Using %(thing)s, the deck can steadily"
#~ " influence more and more vampires, often ending up with 4"
#~ " to 6 vampires in play. Influencing a Baron quickly is"
#~ " very important, but it can be the second vampire if "
#~ "a low capacity can be put in play first to speed "
#~ "up the Baron with a %(thing)s, depending on your opening "
#~ "hand. </p> <p> The number of vampires means naked bleeds "
#~ "provide decent forward pressure. This completes the standard wall"
#~ " payload %(smiling_jack)s and %(constant_revolution)s, and offers some "
#~ "flexibility. </p> <p> The list presented here uses a couple"
#~ " of %(sniper_rifle)s alongside a good number of %(earth_meld)s "
#~ "as combat module, but there are a lot of possible "
#~ "variations for the combat part of the deck. </p> <h2>Tips"
#~ " & Tricks</h2> <p> %(garibaldi_meucci_museum)s is versatile, allowing "
#~ "to fetch the required unlock or bounce. %(powerbase_los_angeles)s "
#~ "acts as cycling device as well as an additional unlock, "
#~ "since there are so many Anarch cards (note Baron cards "
#~ "implicitly count as cards requiring Anarch), and "
#~ "%(the_anarch_free_press)s provides intercept. </p> <p> In terms of "
#~ "ousting power, the deck relies on small bleeds, with "
